    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Filter () - filter the particular set of data based on specific criteria",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "f60d7e84-7036-43ed-bd5d-1791facbb32f",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "You’ll use the Filter formula when you want to use at part of a Table to answer a question. The criteria for this formula can be as simple or as complex as you need.",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "a4f44e3c-6abd-46a9-be54-17bc4e19048d",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "Filter(Table(\"table you want to look at\"), \"criteria matching the part you're interested in\")",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "0c064f11-fc6b-425f-874e-135ed18682a6",
    "type": "bulletListItem",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If () The If formula allows you to handle if/then logic. The basic structure of the If() formula is as follows:",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
    "id": "632f906f-b9c3-45e4-a87c-16074191bcc6",
    "type": "paragraph",
    "props": {
      "textColor": "default",
      "backgroundColor": "default",
      "textAlignment": "left"
    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "If(Condition, \"What you want to happen if this condition is true\", \"What you want to happen if this condition is false\")",
        "styles": {}
      }
    ],
    "children": []
  },
  {
