    },
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "text",
        "text": "In Fundamento tables are in fact databases the smallest unit is a row (unlike in the classic spreadsheets). Working with rows, you’re able to access all of the contextual details for each value (aka columns or attributes of the row).",
        "styles": {}
